---
// Augova — HeroStatic (spec §0.6/§4/§9 `HeroMapStatic`, M11).
// The static, zero-JS hero image: AVIF/WebP, monochrome, same visual
// language as the WebGL mesh/globe. Rendered directly in the server HTML —
// NOT behind client:only — so it's always the hero's LCP paint on every
// device, with zero WebGL/JS cost. WebGL (FluffyGlobeHero) is a progressive
// enhancement layered on top of this by HeroSection, only for capable
// desktop with no reduced-motion preference; everywhere else this image is
// the whole hero visual, exactly per spec ("both must exist and be usable
// on day one").
---

<picture>
  <source srcset="/hero/static.avif" type="image/avif" />
  <source srcset="/hero/static.webp" type="image/webp" />
  <img
    src="/hero/static.webp"
    alt=""
    fetchpriority="high"
    loading="eager"
    decoding="async"
    class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-0 h-full w-full object-cover"
  />
</picture>
